between midnight and 1:00 a.m.

228
00:10:58,484 --> 00:10:59,972
He picks up Cassie Horner,

229
00:10:59,972 --> 00:11:02,688
finishes her off, 
cabs it down to the East Village...

230
00:11:02,688 --> 00:11:05,306
kills Theresa, with plenty 
of time to make the 1:30 ferry...

231
00:11:05,306 --> 00:11:08,432
- back to Staten Island.
- Fredericks isn't our guy.

232
00:11:08,432 --> 00:11:09,399
Based on what?

233
00:11:09,399 --> 00:11:12,228
Lab found two different blood types...
at the last murder scene,

234
00:11:12,228 --> 00:11:16,101
Terry Folsom's and probably the killer's.
Neither matches Fredericks.

235
00:11:16,257 --> 00:11:20,097
Okay. So we book him on the parole
violation for soliciting a prostitute.

236
00:11:20,097 --> 00:11:21,949
And go back to looking 
for the getaway cab.

237
00:11:21,949 --> 00:11:24,754
If this guy's a serial killer, he might
have been active somewhere else.

238
00:11:24,754 --> 00:11:26,779
Check Vi-CAP for any similar MO's.

239
00:11:26,779 --> 00:11:30,544
I'm gonna call Huang,
see if he can't give us a profile.

240
00:11:31,216 --> 00:11:34,194
He comes out at night...
and focuses his rage at prostitutes

241
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:36,862
and women that he...
believes to be prostitutes.

242
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:40,312
- Just like London, 1888.
- Not Jack the Ripper again.

243
00:11:40,312 --> 00:11:43,366
Ripperologists are convinced that...
his Royal Highness,

244
00:11:43,366 --> 00:11:45,604
Prince Albert Victor,
committed the deeds.

245
00:11:45,604 --> 00:11:48,167
And I understand the royal 
family is still smarting over that...

246
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:51,180
- but could we please continue?
- Actually, Captain, our guy...

247
00:11:51,180 --> 00:11:54,433
may be a wannabe. Especially
if he's a paranoid-schizophrenic.

248
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:55,930
How do you explain the fire?

249
00:11:55,930 --> 00:11:58,800
Well, your witnesses say that he 
talked of hell fire and damnation.

250
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:01,689
Maybe he thought that
the victims were the devil.

251
00:12:01,689 --> 00:12:03,198
He didn't torch the second woman.

252
00:12:03,198 --> 00:12:05,567
Well, maybe he heard
footsteps and ran off.

253
00:12:05,567 --> 00:12:07,711
Some witnesses reported that 
he seemed drunk or high.

254
00:12:07,711 --> 00:12:10,199
Well, some schizophrenics
self-medicate with alcohol.

255
00:12:10,199 --> 00:12:11,742
So who we looking for, Doc?

256
00:12:11,742 --> 00:12:15,336
A man mentally ill since 
childhood or early adulthood.

257
00:12:15,336 --> 00:12:17,411
Could possibly have been
institutionalized.

258
00:12:17,411 --> 00:12:20,156
Not able to keep a job. 
Lives alone.

259
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:21,712
Strong religious delusions.

260
00:12:21,712 --> 00:12:25,094
And he might have 
command hallucinations.

261
00:12:25,094 --> 00:12:26,857
Voices telling him to kill.

262
00:12:26,857 --> 00:12:30,571
He's impulsive, disorganized, unpredictable.

263
00:12:31,117 --> 00:12:34,028
And he's not gonna stop
until you catch him.

264
00:12:34,610 --> 00:12:36,241
Better make it soon.

265
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:39,360
The press is already 
calling him the "Night Ripper."

266
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:42,342
- We've gotta release the sketch.
- That would be a mistake.

267
00:12:42,342 --> 00:12:44,766
If people are gonna panic, at least
give them something to panic about.

268
00:12:44,766 --> 00:12:46,602
The publicity's just gonna 
excite him more.

269
00:12:46,602 --> 00:12:50,202
I think he's awful excited
right now without publicity.

270
00:12:50,348 --> 00:12:52,026
We'll consider releasing the sketch.

271
00:12:52,026 --> 00:12:53,786
Meanwhile, I want every vice unit
out warning the working girls to be...

272
00:12:53,786 --> 00:12:57,527
watching out for this guy.
Where are we on the cabs?

273
00:12:57,527 --> 00:12:59,060
We've narrowed it down to 12 possibles,

274
00:12:59,060 --> 00:13:01,282
before we got sidetracked with Fredericks.

275
00:13:01,282 --> 00:13:03,262
Run them down.

276
00:13:03,262 --> 00:13:05,038
Marcus, pick up line six.

277
00:13:05,038 --> 00:13:07,729
No, there's nothing with a Y in the 
number on the street last night.

278
00:13:07,729 --> 00:13:09,954
Okay. How about your V cabs?

279
00:13:09,954 --> 00:13:14,780
Well, we only have two.
Let me look here... Wait.

280
00:13:15,622 --> 00:13:20,507
Wait a minute. Here it is.
5-V-42. Ran 9:00 pm to 9:00 am.

281
00:13:20,507 --> 00:13:22,685
Driver didn't even make 
enough to cover his lease.

282
00:13:22,685 --> 00:13:25,151
Okay, any pickups 
around 44th and 9th?

283
00:13:25,151 --> 00:13:26,981
Uh, not according to his trip sheet.

284
00:13:26,981 --> 00:13:29,696
- Can I take a look at that?
- Be my guest.

285
00:13:32,487 --> 00:13:34,331
Take a look at this.

286
00:13:34,730 --> 00:13:39,548
The driver put 82 miles on the car and
only logged jobs for maybe half of that.

287
00:13:39,548 --> 00:13:41,501
So he didn't drop the 
meter on all of his fares.

288
00:13:41,501 --> 00:13:43,512
This driver.You have a 
name and address for him?

289
00:13:43,512 --> 00:13:46,930
Yeah. Sure. No problem.
I'll get it for you.

290
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:49,348
APARTMENT OF SEKOU OBENG
1815 AMSTERDAM AVENUE
WEDNESDAY, MAY 2

291
00:13:49,348 --> 00:13:51,149
Last night when you 
were driving your cab...

292
00:13:51,149 --> 00:13:54,419
did you pick up a fare
on 44th and 9th Avenue?

293
00:13:54,419 --> 00:13:55,535
No.

294
00:13:55,535 --> 00:13:58,775
You sure? You didn't log more 
than half your jobs on your trip sheet.

295
00:13:58,775 --> 00:14:00,840
What are you talking about?

296
00:14:01,029 --> 00:14:02,859
Maybe you forgot to drop the meter

297
00:14:02,859 --> 00:14:05,410
keep a little more money
for your family?

298
00:14:09,969 --> 00:14:13,555
- I wasn't driving.
- Okay. Who was?

299
00:14:14,259 --> 00:14:17,304
My cousin. Nkrumah?

300
00:14:18,555 --> 00:14:22,981
I pick up the cab, let him drive.

301
00:14:22,981 --> 00:14:26,062
Make some money for 
his family back home.

302
00:14:26,062 --> 00:14:28,806
He pick up the man
you're looking for.

303
00:14:29,093 --> 00:14:31,794
- What's your name?
- Kabral Nkrumah.

304
00:14:31,794 --> 00:14:33,338
Did you see his face?

305
00:14:33,338 --> 00:14:35,638
And his bloody clothes.

306
00:14:35,762 --> 00:14:37,061
He scared me.

307
00:14:37,061 --> 00:14:40,991
Police car drove by, he lowered his 
head so they would not see him.

308
00:14:40,991 --> 00:14:42,574
Okay. Can you describe him?

309
00:14:42,574 --> 00:14:47,185
Medium height...
wild eyes. Wild eyes.

310
00:14:47,185 --> 00:14:49,843
- Bushy beard.
- Where did you take him?

311
00:14:49,843 --> 00:14:51,847
3rd Street and Avenue D.

312
00:14:51,847 --> 00:14:54,520
Paid me with a bloody $20 bill.

313
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:57,319
- Didn't wait for change.
- We're gonna need that bill.

314
00:14:57,319 --> 00:15:00,117
Oh, I spent it.

315
00:15:00,117 --> 00:15:04,289
We're gonna need to get that cab to 
CSU before it goes out for the night.

316
00:15:04,577 --> 00:15:07,472
Find anything? / Yeah, 
we vacuumed for hairs and fibers.

317
00:15:07,472 --> 00:15:10,421
Just getting ready to look for blood.
Let me light it up.

318
00:15:10,421 --> 00:15:11,912
If the guy had victim's 
blood on his coat,

319
00:15:11,912 --> 00:15:13,977
he must've gotten some on his hands.

320
00:15:13,977 --> 00:15:17,385
Munch. / Or he slipped and cut
himself, left us some evidence.

321
00:15:17,385 --> 00:15:20,304
Look, blood. I'll lift it 
and get it to the lab.

322
00:15:20,304 --> 00:15:22,035
Yeah. We'll be right there. 
Gotta go. / What?

323
00:15:22,035 --> 00:15:24,110
Jack strikes again.

324
00:15:26,761 --> 00:15:29,458
I'm washing my hands,
the kid is at the urinal.

325
00:15:29,458 --> 00:15:30,870
Guy comes in and 
starts screaming about

326
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:33,381
the machines controlling the boy's mind...

327
00:15:33,381 --> 00:15:36,588
pulls out a knife, slits 
his throat. Just like that.

328
00:15:36,588 --> 00:15:38,945
- Did he go after you next?
- I went after him,

329
00:15:38,945 --> 00:15:41,734
tried to grab the knife.
He got me in the stomach.

330
00:15:41,734 --> 00:15:44,358
- That's when the boy's father comes in.
- What happened?

331
00:15:44,358 --> 00:15:46,205
He never saw the guy with the knife.

332
00:15:46,205 --> 00:15:48,450
He runs straight for his kid, 
starts screaming.

333
00:15:48,450 --> 00:15:50,745
I'm yelling at him about the knife...

334
00:15:50,990 --> 00:15:54,446
then the guy slices his neck.
I couldn't do nothing!

335
00:15:54,446 --> 00:15:56,915
- You did plenty. Take it easy.
- We're gonna ride with him.

336
00:15:56,915 --> 00:15:58,831
- Yeah. All right. 
- What took you so long?

337
00:15:58,831 --> 00:16:01,083
We were in Queens.
We found the cab driver.

338
00:16:01,083 --> 00:16:02,502
Huang is on his way.

339
00:16:02,502 --> 00:16:05,589
Says he can profile more 
accurately if he's on the scene.

340
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:08,430
- Radio said two victims?
- Well, almost three.

341
00:16:08,430 --> 00:16:11,590
Good Samaritan got stabbed
in the gut trying to stop him.

342
00:16:12,306 --> 00:16:13,417
Who's she?

343
00:16:13,417 --> 00:16:18,757
This is Jean Weston. It's her 
husband and son cut up in there.

344
00:16:18,757 --> 00:16:21,931
Tourists. / I thought  
he was targeting pros.

345
00:16:22,788 --> 00:16:24,734
How old's the kid?  /  Nine.

346
00:16:24,734 --> 00:16:27,194
Son of a bitch.

347
00:16:29,241 --> 00:16:32,014
Mrs. Weston, I'm Detective Stabler.

348
00:16:33,441 --> 00:16:37,211
Josh just wanted to play video games.

349
00:16:38,082 --> 00:16:40,086
We're going back to 
Oregon tomorrow morning.

350
00:16:40,086 --> 00:16:41,800
I have to go pack.

351
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:45,033
Okay, I'll tell you what.
We're gonna have the officer take you...

352
00:16:45,033 --> 00:16:48,476
to the hospital first and just 
have you checked out.

353
00:16:49,442 --> 00:16:51,391
Okay?

354
00:17:03,168 --> 00:17:05,462
Got him in the left carotid.

355
00:17:05,462 --> 00:17:09,316
He probably lived about two
minutes before he bled out.

356
00:17:09,316 --> 00:17:10,839
Same knife?

357
00:17:11,835 --> 00:17:13,676
Yeah.

358
00:17:18,282 --> 00:17:21,089
Four victims within 24 hours.

359
00:17:21,089 --> 00:17:23,596
Three in the theater district,
Times Square area...

360
00:17:23,596 --> 00:17:25,178
one in the East Village.

361
00:17:25,178 --> 00:17:28,946
And a serial killer we can't profile 
because he strikes at random.

362
00:17:29,077 --> 00:17:30,415
It doesn't get much worse than this.

363
00:17:30,415 --> 00:17:34,224
Nobody is safe until we 
collar this guy. Chief Sullivan?

364
00:17:34,224 --> 00:17:37,303
The city is terrified, and the public 
doesn't give a rat's ass how much...

365
00:17:37,303 --> 00:17:40,493
we brought crime down as
long as this guy is out there.

366
00:17:40,584 --> 00:17:42,548
I want to thank all of you 
who came in on your own time.

367
00:17:42,548 --> 00:17:45,242
Clock in. We need 
all the help we can get.

368
00:17:45,242 --> 00:17:48,732
Captain Cragen runs the task 
force and reports directly to me.

369
00:17:48,732 --> 00:17:52,705
The phone bank is being set up, 
with the reward up to $100,000.

370
00:17:52,705 --> 00:17:56,077
We're gonna be flooded with tips
We investigate every one.

371
00:17:56,180 --> 00:17:59,012
You have your assignments.
Let's find this guy.

372
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:01,014
What'd you get?

373
00:18:01,863 --> 00:18:03,519
Canvass, Avenue D.

374
00:18:04,217 --> 00:18:05,735
Canvass on Avenue C.

375
00:18:05,735 --> 00:18:07,848
I'm Avenue B. You're Avenue A, 
I guess.

376
00:18:07,848 --> 00:18:11,157
Palmieri's taking Avenue A. 
Anything from Vi-CAP?

377
00:18:11,157 --> 00:18:12,551
Nobody active fitting our guy.

378
00:18:12,551 --> 00:18:13,820
Yeah. That would've been too easy.

379
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:17,776
John, before you hit the streets,
I want you to get an update from the ME.

380
00:18:17,776 --> 00:18:20,640
- Okay, Boss. See you guys later.
- All right. / - Set?

381
00:18:21,546 --> 00:18:24,336
I want you coordinating the 
phone tips and the assignments.

382
00:18:24,336 --> 00:18:27,350
Our case, then why am I being benched?

383
00:18:27,350 --> 00:18:30,974
I need somebody I can trust
in charge while I tap-dance for the bosses.

384
00:18:30,974 --> 00:18:33,717
Nobody sweats the details like you.

385
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:36,973
Okay. Go get him.

386
00:18:37,501 --> 00:18:39,825
- Detective Stabler.
- Mrs. Weston.

387
00:18:39,946 --> 00:18:41,654
I said you were busy.

388
00:18:41,654 --> 00:18:45,053
We're closing on our new house
next week. I have to get home.

389
00:18:45,053 --> 00:18:47,220
Mrs. Weston, do you have any relatives

390
00:18:47,220 --> 00:18:49,618
or friends in New York 
you can stay with?

391
00:18:49,618 --> 00:18:52,678
I don't know anyone here.

392
00:18:52,678 --> 00:18:56,870
I don't... / Elliott. Phone call.

393
00:18:58,091 --> 00:19:01,601
Mrs. Weston, this is 
Detective Palmieri. Right here.

394
00:19:01,601 --> 00:19:04,553
He's gonna get you coffee,
food, whatever you want.

395
00:19:04,553 --> 00:19:06,530
I'll be with you in just a minute, okay?

396
00:19:07,417 --> 00:19:09,058
See if you can find a family member.

397
00:19:09,058 --> 00:19:12,163
Okay. Why don't you come with me?

398
00:19:17,758 --> 00:19:22,014
Special Victims, 
Detective... Hey, Kathy.

399
00:19:23,122 --> 00:19:25,950
No. It's just good to hear your voice.

400
00:19:26,293 --> 00:19:28,865
The unidentified blood at the 
second murder scene and the blood...

401
00:19:28,865 --> 00:19:31,511
CSU got from the cab 
are the same type. AB.

402
00:19:31,511 --> 00:19:34,041
Which puts our man at the first 
two scenes. We won the trifecta.

403
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:36,442
We found only the victim's
blood at the arcade,

404
00:19:36,442 --> 00:19:38,897
but take a look at these.
You know Locard's theory?

405
00:19:38,897 --> 00:19:40,324
Transfer evidence.
Everywhere you go

406
00:19:40,324 --> 00:19:42,150
you pick something up 
and leave something behind.

407
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:44,049
Seven years in Homicide,
I better know it.

408
00:19:44,049 --> 00:19:48,009
CSU took this from inside the 
perp's coat found in the garbage can.

409
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:50,065
This was on the body of Terry Folsom...

410
00:19:50,065 --> 00:19:53,092
and this was in the pooled blood 
next to Josh and Jeremy Weston.

411
00:19:53,092 --> 00:19:55,300
Consistent blends.
Some kind of spun fiber.

412
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:59,387
Ran it through the gas chromatograph.
It's a 60-40 cotton wool blend.

413
00:19:59,387 --> 00:20:02,023
I'm a summer weight
wool-gabardine man myself.

414
00:20:02,023 --> 00:20:06,068
Your perp wore the same piece of 
clothing when he killed all four victims.

415
00:20:07,642 --> 00:20:08,993
Thanks.

416
00:20:11,430 --> 00:20:13,383
Forget the canvass.

417
00:20:13,383 --> 00:20:15,461
We got a disturbance in 
Washington Square Park.

418
00:20:15,461 --> 00:20:19,698
A suspect in the murders is being 
held by civilians. Let's get there now.

419
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:21,770
Special Victims. Excuse me! Police.

420
00:20:21,770 --> 00:20:24,026
- Coming through. Excuse me.
- Show's over!  / Excuse me.

421
00:20:24,248 --> 00:20:26,438
Bus is on the way along 
with the rest of our backup.

422
00:20:26,438 --> 00:20:27,823
What the hell happened here?

423
00:20:27,823 --> 00:20:30,771
Someone heard this guy accost 
a pro over on 4th Street,

424
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:34,678
spouting something about Armageddon.
Next thing, a dozen people

425
00:20:34,678 --> 00:20:37,684
they chase him in here,
and they kick the crap out of him.

426
00:20:37,684 --> 00:20:38,852
He's not even close.

427
00:20:38,852 --> 00:20:42,802
Okay, people. Look at this.
This is our man. Beard and hair.

428
00:20:42,802 --> 00:20:46,004
- This man has no beard and no hair.
- Bastard shaved it off!

429
00:20:46,004 --> 00:20:48,630
- Yeah! 
- Tried to kill another whore!

430
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:49,943
Who's gonna be next?

431
00:20:49,943 --> 00:20:52,695
Get outta here or both you are going
in for assault, all right? All of you.

432
00:20:52,695 --> 00:20:55,128
Hang in there, all right?
The ambulance is on its way.

433
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:57,246
Just take it easy, okay?

434
00:20:57,938 --> 00:21:00,406
These people have a serious problem.

435
00:21:00,406 --> 00:21:02,247
Yeah, they're scared.

436
00:21:03,577 --> 00:21:07,004
Hey. / Hey, you survived riot duty.

437
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:09,050
Hope you had better luck than we did.

438
00:21:09,050 --> 00:21:10,361
How's it going?

439
00:21:10,361 --> 00:21:14,221
Five hundred calls since 11:00,
more sightings than Elvis.

440
00:21:14,221 --> 00:21:15,906
Anyone wanna trade places?

441
00:21:15,906 --> 00:21:18,407
No thanks. We're just too 
busy waiting for him to strike again.

442
00:21:18,407 --> 00:21:22,725
Look, it's 4:00. Why don't you 
guys catch some shut-eye?

443
00:21:22,725 --> 00:21:25,291
Don't have to ask me twice.

444
00:21:25,291 --> 00:21:27,207
Not at home, in the crib.

445
00:21:34,678 --> 00:21:38,374
You, too. / Oh, no.
I'm too pissed to sleep.

446
00:21:38,374 --> 00:21:40,634
You want some help?

447
00:21:40,634 --> 00:21:42,870
I'm not gonna say no.

448
00:21:49,518 --> 00:21:52,403
"Spotted on Broadway."

449
00:21:52,534 --> 00:21:56,120
"It looks like the subway
token clerk at 68th and Lex."

450
00:21:57,307 --> 00:21:58,883
"He's my night doorman."

451
00:21:58,883 --> 00:22:00,595
I know you're working 
off some nervous energy...

452
00:22:00,595 --> 00:22:03,207
but you don't have to
read every one of them out loud.

453
00:22:06,312 --> 00:22:08,520
Aren't we in a mood?

454
00:22:12,345 --> 00:22:16,688
You know, it's the middle of 
the night, and I'm sitting here

455
00:22:16,688 --> 00:22:20,822
realizing I spend more time with 
you than I do with my own family...

456
00:22:21,557 --> 00:22:23,263
No offense.

457
00:22:23,263 --> 00:22:25,606
We both need a vacation.

458
00:22:26,924 --> 00:22:28,880
You got that right.

459
00:22:32,037 --> 00:22:34,957
Wait a minute. 
Here's one with a guy...

460
00:22:34,957 --> 00:22:38,726
