00:36:33,659 --> 00:36:35,485
What about?

706
00:36:36,174 --> 00:36:39,747
You were right, Mrs. Varney.

707
00:36:40,134 --> 00:36:42,694
It wasn't your husband's fault.

708
00:36:43,551 --> 00:36:46,672
Mrs. Varney, your husband has syphilis.

709
00:36:47,486 --> 00:36:52,455
- Oh, my God.
- It's destroyed his brain.

710
00:36:54,234 --> 00:36:57,016
Well, what does that mean?
What about my daughters?

711
00:36:57,016 --> 00:36:59,554
What about me? 
We've been married for ten years.

712
00:36:59,554 --> 00:37:00,672
You'll have to be tested,

713
00:37:00,672 --> 00:37:03,248
but our doctor says that
it's only contagious...

714
00:37:03,248 --> 00:37:05,375
in the early stages.

715
00:37:05,375 --> 00:37:07,276
Your husband's case is so advanced...

716
00:37:07,276 --> 00:37:10,953
that he probably picked it up
long before you even met.

717
00:37:11,281 --> 00:37:14,717
I don't understand.
How could no one find this?

718
00:37:14,717 --> 00:37:17,291
He's been to doctors,
he had an insurance physical...

719
00:37:17,291 --> 00:37:20,502
- Medical insurance?
- Life insurance.

720
00:37:20,502 --> 00:37:22,235
Seven years ago,

721
00:37:22,235 --> 00:37:24,365
when our first daughter was born.

722
00:37:24,365 --> 00:37:27,452
- Was he approved?  
- No.

723
00:37:27,964 --> 00:37:31,184
Well, did the insurance 
company ever tell you why?

724
00:37:32,452 --> 00:37:35,913
We thought it had to do 
with his hypertension.

725
00:37:35,913 --> 00:37:37,601
Mrs. Varney, if you ask
the insurance company...

726
00:37:37,601 --> 00:37:41,051
why your husband was rejected, 
they have to tell you.

727
00:37:42,067 --> 00:37:44,483
- Does it really matter now?
- Yes. It really matters.

728
00:37:44,483 --> 00:37:47,476
You've got to request those records.

729
00:37:59,018 --> 00:38:00,713
I missed you.

730
00:38:00,713 --> 00:38:03,487
Hi, honey. Me, too.

731
00:38:03,779 --> 00:38:07,393
- The girls miss their daddy.
- How are they?

732
00:38:07,393 --> 00:38:10,906
They're fine. How are you?

733
00:38:12,564 --> 00:38:15,134
It hurts so much.

734
00:38:17,649 --> 00:38:20,062
I'm sorry.

735
00:38:34,746 --> 00:38:37,493
Paula Varney got an answer
from All-Atlantic Life.

736
00:38:37,493 --> 00:38:39,238
They knew that he had syphilis.

737
00:38:39,238 --> 00:38:40,919
Bastards never informed him.

738
00:38:40,919 --> 00:38:42,929
Communicable, sexually 
transmitted disease,

739
00:38:42,929 --> 00:38:45,451
company's required to report that 
to the health department.

740
00:38:45,451 --> 00:38:48,999
And health department would have 
notified Varney if they'd known.

741
00:38:48,999 --> 00:38:51,542
One shot of penicillin back then 
could have cured him.

742
00:38:51,542 --> 00:38:53,400
And these four victim
swould still be alive.

743
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:56,118
Yeah, if the insurance
company had told them!

744
00:38:56,408 --> 00:38:58,727
I want their ass.

745
00:39:00,822 --> 00:39:04,900
OFFICE OF MALCOLM HUNT CEO
ALL-ATLANTIC LIFE
INSURANCE COMPANY
TUESDAY, MAY 8

746
00:39:07,170 --> 00:39:09,301
- What is this?   
- Malcolm Hunt?

747
00:39:09,301 --> 00:39:11,282
- And who are you?  
- Police.

748
00:39:11,282 --> 00:39:12,898
Come up from behind the desk, please.

749
00:39:12,898 --> 00:39:14,268
I don't take orders from you.

750
00:39:14,268 --> 00:39:17,076
Malcolm Hunt, you're under 
arrest for reckless endangerment.

751
00:39:17,076 --> 00:39:18,951
Reckless endangerment? 
For what?

752
00:39:18,951 --> 00:39:22,888
For failing to notify the health department 
about an applicant's communicable disease

753
00:39:22,888 --> 00:39:24,905
which caused him to murder four people.

754
00:39:24,905 --> 00:39:27,217
How dare you walk in here 
and accuse me...

755
00:39:27,217 --> 00:39:28,612
Your lawyer can explain it to you.

756
00:39:28,612 --> 00:39:31,229
No, you're the ones who can explain.
On whose authority?

757
00:39:31,229 --> 00:39:32,955
We have a warrant, signed by a judge.

758
00:39:32,955 --> 00:39:35,243
And if you don't come with 
us voluntarily, we'll take you.

759
00:39:35,243 --> 00:39:37,149
Now please put your 
hands behind your back.

760
00:39:37,149 --> 00:39:39,080
Is this necessary?

761
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:41,187
Standard procedure.

762
00:39:41,401 --> 00:39:42,935
You have the right to remain silent.

763
00:39:42,935 --> 00:39:44,327
If you give up that right,
anything you say

764
00:39:44,327 --> 00:39:47,691
can and will beused against 
youin a court of law.

765
00:39:47,805 --> 00:39:50,922
You need a head to mount on your wall

766
00:39:50,922 --> 00:39:53,938
so my client becomes the scapegoat.

767
00:39:54,324 --> 00:39:56,175
We checked with the 
health department.

768
00:39:56,175 --> 00:39:59,511
You never reported Daniel Varney's 
syphilis as required by law...

769
00:39:59,511 --> 00:40:00,933
It must have slipped 
through the cracks.

770
00:40:00,933 --> 00:40:04,563
It's the applicant's responsibility 
to ask why he was rejected.

771
00:40:04,563 --> 00:40:06,362
Who's responsible for the 
four people he murdered

772
00:40:06,362 --> 00:40:07,982
because you didn't tell him?

773
00:40:07,982 --> 00:40:10,817
We reject thousands of 
applicants every year.

774
00:40:10,817 --> 00:40:13,874
- HIV, heart disease.
- All poor risks.

775
00:40:13,874 --> 00:40:16,293
Miss Cabot, we run a business.

776
00:40:16,293 --> 00:40:18,892
We answer to our stockholders.

777
00:40:18,892 --> 00:40:23,206
Providing explanations to 
every applicant we turn down

778
00:40:23,206 --> 00:40:25,631
would require hiring more staff

779
00:40:25,631 --> 00:40:28,029
premiums would go through 
the roof, and fewer people

780
00:40:28,029 --> 00:40:31,542
could afford life insurance.

781
00:40:31,542 --> 00:40:34,671
$1.50 worth of penicillin would 
have cured Daniel Varney...

782
00:40:34,671 --> 00:40:37,455
and prevented the carnage he caused.

783
00:40:37,455 --> 00:40:38,757
You should have told him.

784
00:40:38,757 --> 00:40:42,674
The Court of Appeals just ruled that 
we are under no obligation to inform the...

785
00:40:42,674 --> 00:40:47,438
The applicant. You still have to notify 
the appropriate health department.

786
00:40:47,438 --> 00:40:50,077
If we audit your records and
find a pattern of similar cases

787
00:40:50,077 --> 00:40:51,257
that have "slipped through the cracks"

788
00:40:51,257 --> 00:40:54,799
with no effort on the part of your 
company to rectify the situation,

789
00:40:54,799 --> 00:40:57,302
not only will we charge Mr. Hunt
with reckless endangerment,

790
00:40:57,302 --> 00:41:01,147
we will move to seize the profits of 
your company as assets to the crime.

791
00:41:01,147 --> 00:41:02,635
See how your stockholders like that.

792
00:41:02,635 --> 00:41:07,659
You can't do that... / And Mr. Hunt can sit 
in prison for seven years and think about it.

793
00:41:11,416 --> 00:41:13,932
What do you want, Miss Cabot?

794
00:41:13,932 --> 00:41:18,048
I want your company to begin reporting 
all cases of communicable diseases.

795
00:41:18,048 --> 00:41:21,470
And when the families of the murder 
victims and Daniel Varney's wife sue...

796
00:41:21,470 --> 00:41:23,368
you'll settle.

797
00:41:23,368 --> 00:41:26,498
That's extortion. It would 
cost the company millions.

798
00:41:26,498 --> 00:41:30,010
It'll cost a lot less than going
bankrupt because of the publicity.

799
00:41:30,010 --> 00:41:32,933
In the court of public opinion,
you're already guilty.

800
00:41:32,933 --> 00:41:36,221
Do you want to take your
chances in a real court?

801
00:41:42,891 --> 00:41:46,887
